topic.title: Port Equalization Control Command

body.p: MRPC Command ID: 0x15
Sub Command 0 is reserved

p.b: Sub Command: Link Tuning Method Configuration

body.p: Switch upstream port will tune transmitter setting of far-end downstream port such as a root port or a upstream switch’s downstream port in phase 2; while switch downstream port will tune transmitter setting of far-end upstream port such as an end point Endpoint or a downstream switch’s upstream port in phase 3. Switchtec provides the following tuning methods.

li.p: Preset Mode, preset will be tuned from 0-”Maximum Preset“, which can be configured up to be 10. In this mode, “Use_COEF” can be further configured. If “Use_COEF” is configured to be 1, “Use Preset” bit in TS1 Ordered Sets will be 0 during equalization of phase 2(USP)/3(DSP), and preset value is invalid, while pre-cursor and post-cursor are valid. If “Use_COEF” is configured to be 0, “Use Preset” bit in TS1 Ordered Sets will be 1 during equalization of phase 2(USP)/3(DSP), and preset value is valid, while pre-cursor and post-cursor are invalid.

Algorithm Mode, In this mode, a couple of ”Maximum Pre-Cursor“ and ”Maximum Post-Cursor“ are specified, the tuning algorithm will step them from 0 to them sequentially with an individual step size individually specified by “Pre-Cursor Step” and “Post-Cursor Step".

Table Method, Different to “Preset Method” and “Algorithm Method”, a table, instead of a maximum value, is provided to make tuning algorithm traverse the table with a "Maximum Table Index", which can be configured up to 23. A table entry includes the following members:
Preset_COEF:
0 - This entry is using Preset value
1 - This entry is using Coefficient value
if Preset_COEF is 0, this field contains a valid Preset value, else, it contains a valid Pre-Cursor of coefficient value.
if Preset_COEF is 0, this field is invalid, else, it contains a valid Post-Cursor of coefficient value.

table.title: Sub Command_Link Tuning Method Configuration Input Data

li.p: the descriptions for the input data.
0x00： Link Tuning Method Configuration
Physical port id, 0-51
0: Gen3; 1: Gen4
0: Preset
1: Algorithm
2: Table
When tune method is "Preset", it represents "maximum preset"
When tune method is "Algorithm", it represents "maximum Pre-Cursor"
When tune method is "Table", it represents "maximum Table Index"
Only valid when tune method is "Algorithm", working together with "Maximum Pre-Cursor"
Only valid when tune method is "Preset', COEF will be internally converted from the preset value before send with EQ TS1/TS2
Only valid when tune method is "Algorithm", it represent the step size. The pre-cursor/post-cursor will be increased by the step size each time.

p.b: Only valid when tune method is "Table". One table entry is composed of the three items.

li.p: Preset_COEF: 0 - Preset; 1 - COEF
PreCursor/Preset:
Preset when Preset_COEF is 0
Pre-Cursor when Preset_COEF is 1
PostCursor:
Post-Cursor

p.b: Sub Command: Local Tx Coefficient Override

body.p: This Sub Command provides the configuration interface individually for Gen 3 and Gen 4 to override the local transmitter coefficient value even after a successful link equalization process. But the “Enable Override” are shared by Gen 3 and Gen 4, which means that both Gen 3 and Gen 4 local coefficient override in Serdes must be enabled/disabled simultaneously, though the override value can be configured individually.

table.title: Sub Command_Local Transmitter Coefficient Override Input Data

body.p: 0x01： Local Tx Coefficient Override
0: Per port operation; 1: Per lane operation
If per port operation is selected, all the parameters will be applied to all the lanes in current port.
Physical port id, 0-51
Logical lane ID in current physical port, 0 - maximum link width
Only valid when operation type is 1
0: Disable local coefficient override; 1: Enable local coefficient override
Gen3 Pre Cursor to be overridden with
Gen3 Post Cursor to be overridden with
Gen4 Pre Cursor to be overridden with
Gen4 Post Cursor to be overridden with

p.b: Sub Command: Far-End Transmitter Preset Override

body.p: This Sub Command provides an interface to override transmitter preset of far-end side. Currently only a per-port operation is supported. It will enhanced to support a per-lane operation in the future. Therefore currently, no matter what value ”Op Type" and "Lane ID" are configured to be, only a per-port operation will be applied.

table.title: Sub Command_Far-End Transmitter Preset Override Input Data

body.p: 0x02： Far-End Tx Preset Override
0: Per port operation; 1: Per lane operation
If per port operation is selected, all the parameters will be applied to all the lanes in current port.
Physical port id, 0-51
Logical lane ID in current physical port, 0 - maximum link width
Only valid when operation type is 1
0: Disable far-end preset override; 1: Enable far-end preset override
Preset value to be overridden with
